{
  "stem": "6878.4",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And we were driven on to the airport, and we had to unload a lot of railway trucks of cement.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Each bag of the cement weighs 50 kilos, and there were quite a number of elderly people.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And it wasn't so easy for them to schlep 50 kilos, and the Germans stood behind and pushed us to run quickly with the bags.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "That night, we lost about 250 people.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "What had happened, they used to go with the bag of cement and drop.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And once they dropped it, the officer in charge would come up, pull out his gun, and shoot him in the head and put his foot down.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And that was the end.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We were then kept right through the day-- right through the night and right through the day.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "We didn't believe it, that we were going to be driven back to the ghettos.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "We had in our mind, from there, they'll take us to the-- to the-- whatever, and they will-- they will shoot us.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But they brought us back to the airport-- to the ghetto, and we continued work again, the same, the daily work again, from different-- we lost a lot of people that night.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "One day, before the-- we-- the last days of the war in Lithuania, the German communication-- post-communication moved in into the building-- into the house where we were.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we were in one room, and the other room were the German communications.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They didn't ask any questions.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They just moved in, and that's it.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[INAUDIBLE] houses in our little coal [INAUDIBLE], and they're burning.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we're afraid that our house will be-- will be hit in the next-- we don't know when-- and you-- and the house will catch fire.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And you will-- you will die in that hole.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
